00:39:05,494 --> 00:39:08,677
After Civ 3 shipped, I really embedded myself into the Civ

787
00:39:08,677 --> 00:39:12,561
community, found some of the best voices in the community

788
00:39:12,561 --> 00:39:15,224
and helped them guide me to know how to basically patch Civ 3.

789
00:39:15,224 --> 00:39:18,307
So then the next step was, well, let's bring these people

790
00:39:18,307 --> 00:39:21,110
on board, create sort of this private testing group where

791
00:39:21,110 --> 00:39:22,471
they could play Civ 4 early.

792
00:39:22,471 --> 00:39:23,673
And I mean really early.

793
00:39:23,673 --> 00:39:25,354
They played it in the first half of the project.

794
00:39:27,036 --> 00:39:30,078
it was, Civ 4 was about a two and a half year development

795
00:39:30,078 --> 00:39:32,460
cycle and they played it at about the 12 month,

796
00:39:32,460 --> 00:39:33,501
you know, 12 months after development.

797
00:39:33,501 --> 00:39:35,302
So they played it when it was really early,

798
00:39:35,302 --> 00:39:38,225
it was really ugly, but I think that's the key reason

799
00:39:38,225 --> 00:39:42,007
why Civ 4 was really well received,

800
00:39:42,007 --> 00:39:44,930
is that we had this great iteration time

801
00:39:44,930 --> 00:39:46,911
with the fan community, you know,

802
00:39:46,911 --> 00:39:49,353
with actual players who are outside of the team

803
00:39:49,353 --> 00:39:50,414
and didn't have all the prejudices

804
00:39:50,414 --> 00:39:51,475
you have inside of your team.

805
00:39:53,692 --> 00:39:57,695
And we saw this immediately once we went up on early access,

806
00:39:57,695 --> 00:40:00,737
that we were blind to certain problems in the game.

807
00:40:00,737 --> 00:40:02,779
And probably the most obvious example of this

808
00:40:02,779 --> 00:40:04,900
is the reveal map option.

809
00:40:04,900 --> 00:40:08,743
So the way we had made Offworld was it has a scanning mode

810
00:40:08,743 --> 00:40:09,583
when the game begins,

811
00:40:09,583 --> 00:40:11,204
which is basically the exploration part,

812
00:40:11,204 --> 00:40:12,826
and you just start clicking around the map,

813
00:40:12,826 --> 00:40:15,187
revealing tiles slowly,

814
00:40:15,187 --> 00:40:17,149
until you find what you think is a good founding location.

815
00:40:17,149 --> 00:40:19,070
And that works great in single player,

816
00:40:19,070 --> 00:40:20,611
but the multiplayer community

817
00:40:20,611 --> 00:40:22,012
just found it completely unacceptable.

818
00:40:22,252 --> 00:40:23,694
because basically you imagine two players,

819
00:40:23,694 --> 00:40:25,297
one of them scans one direction,

820
00:40:25,297 --> 00:40:26,639
one of them scans the other direction.

821
00:40:26,639 --> 00:40:30,044
The person who went east finds a great founding location,

822
00:40:30,044 --> 00:40:31,446
puts down their headquarters.

823
00:40:31,446 --> 00:40:33,769
Person who went west feels like they lost the game

824
00:40:33,769 --> 00:40:37,214
because they just randomly went the wrong direction.

825
00:40:37,214 --> 00:40:39,315
we had game mechanics to basically balance that.

826
00:40:39,315 --> 00:40:40,595
Of like, well, whoever found second,

827
00:40:40,595 --> 00:40:42,715
you get extra claims and so on and so forth.

828
00:40:42,715 --> 00:40:44,816
But the main thing is perception.

829
00:40:44,816 --> 00:40:46,196
Like at that point, perception is reality.

830
00:40:46,196 --> 00:40:47,676
It felt unfair to people.

831
00:40:47,676 --> 00:40:48,677
So we tried something different.

832
00:40:48,677 --> 00:40:50,437
And this happened like within a month or two

833
00:40:50,437 --> 00:40:51,077
of early access.

834
00:40:51,077 --> 00:40:52,877
We like, we know we gotta do something about this.

835
00:40:52,877 --> 00:40:55,498
So I came up with the reveal map option,

836
00:40:55,498 --> 00:40:56,838
which means that basically the game,

837
00:40:56,838 --> 00:40:59,159
the map starts completely revealed

838
00:40:59,159 --> 00:41:01,379
and you have basically kind of like a reverse auction

839
00:41:01,379 --> 00:41:04,100
that you could found immediately if you want to,

840
00:41:04,100 --> 00:41:05,620
but you're gonna have to take on $200,000 of debt.

841
00:41:06,460 --> 00:41:07,921
And that price is just gonna get,

842
00:41:07,921 --> 00:41:09,702
kind of like slowly ticked down.

843
00:41:09,702 --> 00:41:11,903
I got this idea I think from Frozen Synapse,

844
00:41:11,903 --> 00:41:13,404
they have kind of like a similar idea of like,

845
00:41:13,404 --> 00:41:15,244
you know, show the whole map and then you kind of bid

846
00:41:15,244 --> 00:41:17,225
on the different starting location.

847
00:41:17,225 --> 00:41:19,066
But like, you know, basically the number kind of

848
00:41:19,066 --> 00:41:21,627
keeps ticking down until it gets to the point

849
00:41:21,627 --> 00:41:25,289
where you're like, well, I think the best spot on the map

850
00:41:25,289 --> 00:41:26,630
is worth say $40,000 of debt, so you're able to,

851
00:41:26,630 --> 00:41:27,650
you know, so you commit.

852
00:41:27,650 --> 00:41:29,211
You're the first mover, you get it.

853
00:41:29,211 --> 00:41:30,851
And then you find out if you made the right choice,

854
00:41:30,851 --> 00:41:32,112
you know, over the course of the game.

855
00:41:33,100 --> 00:41:36,681
And that worked. The multiple computer were like, yes, that's

856
00:41:36,681 --> 00:41:40,541
it. That's the way they play the game, period. And if we had been

857
00:41:40,541 --> 00:41:44,422
a traditional game where we didn't go through early access,

858
00:41:44,422 --> 00:41:49,023
we would have found this out two months after launch instead of

859
00:41:49,023 --> 00:41:51,444
12 months before launch. That makes a pretty big difference

860
00:41:51,444 --> 00:41:55,265
because we then had 12 months to iterate on just this option

861
00:41:55,265 --> 00:41:58,946
itself. It became a core part of the game instead of a hacky fix

862
00:41:58,946 --> 00:42:00,086
that we had to do post launch.

863
00:42:02,648 --> 00:42:07,430
Another thing that was really important is that I knew we were going to make major changes in

864
00:42:07,430 --> 00:42:12,873
early access and there have been games in early access that have made major changes that have

865
00:42:12,873 --> 00:42:16,855
really upset their community. And this is a hard thing. There's no simple answer here because

866
00:42:16,855 --> 00:42:20,197
the community thinks they have one game, they're happy with it, so the game changes.

867
00:42:20,477 --> 00:42:22,539
what, you know, like, and if they're unhappy with it,

868
00:42:22,539 --> 00:42:24,421
it can lead to, you know, it can lead to some really

869
00:42:24,421 --> 00:42:26,543
bad feelings, some bad reviews,

870
00:42:26,543 --> 00:42:28,004
lead to controversy, basically.

871
00:42:28,004 --> 00:42:29,846
We didn't want that to happen,

872
00:42:29,846 --> 00:42:31,928
so what we did is anytime we had some major change

